title: Google\Cloud\Dlp\V2\ContentLocation
name: ContentLocation
description:
Precise location of the finding within a document, record, image, or metadata container.

Generated from protobuf message google.privacy.dlp.v2.ContentLocation

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.container_name
params.description: Name of the container where the finding is located. The top level name is the source file name or table name. Names of some common storage containers are formatted as follows: BigQuery tables: {project_id}:{dataset_id}.{table_id} Cloud Storage files: gs://{bucket}/{path} * Datastore namespace: {namespace} Nested names could be absent if the embedded object has no string identifier (for an example an image contained within a document).

params.name: data.record_location
params.description: Location within a row or record of a database table.

params.name: data.metadata_location
params.description: Location within the metadata for inspected content.

params.name: data.container_timestamp
params.description: Findings container modification timestamp, if applicable. For Google Cloud Storage contains last file modification timestamp. For BigQuery table contains last_modified_time property. For Datastore - not populated.

params.name: data.container_version
params.description: Findings container version, if available ("generation" for Google Cloud Storage).
